<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 16 at 1:57PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of
northwestern Roanoke, Craig, west central Botetourt and southeastern
Monroe Counties through 230 PM EDT...
At 157 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Waiteville, or near Paint Bank, moving east at 45 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
New Castle...
Paint Bank...
Catawba...
Sinking Creek...
Abbott...
Hollywood...
and Craig Springs.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
